          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to calculate the surplus or deficit of a budget based on the actual usage and the allocated budget. Scalar functions return a single value and are typically used in SELECT statements or as part of a larger query to perform calculations or transformations on data."
